WEBVTT

00:58.392 --> 00:59.477
SHAGGY:
That's my pal.

01:00.061 --> 01:01.646
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

01:28.464 --> 01:30.174
WOMAN:
No, | didn't.

01:30.341 --> 01:32.134
The cat. I--

01:32.301 --> 01:34.178
The cat.

01:35.304 --> 01:36.806
It wasn't me.

01:36.973 --> 01:39.934
The cat. Oh.

01:49.277 --> 01:52.238
[SNARLING]

02:11.132 --> 02:12.174
Cab!

02:12.341 --> 02:14.260
Hey, taxi.

02:14.468 --> 02:18.264
Yoo-hoo! We need a cab here.

02:19.265 --> 02:20.683
It's no use, guys.

02:20.850 --> 02:24.020
We'll never get a cab in New York
with a storm coming.

02:24.186 --> 02:26.981
SHAGGY: Well, at least we won't starve
while we wait.

02:27.148 --> 02:31.527
Scooby and | found a place
that sells mile-long hot dogs.

02:32.069 --> 02:34.405
Yeah, mile-long.

02:37.325 --> 02:40.286
Yum, hot dog.

02:43.539 --> 02:45.124
-Whoops.
-Scooby...

02:45.291 --> 02:47.501
...you ate the whole hot dog yourself.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.754
Not yet.

02:53.799 --> 02:55.676
Ahh. Now.

02:55.885 --> 02:59.180
SHAGGY: Like, thanks a lot, old pal,
old buddy, old Scoob.

02:59.347 --> 03:00.556
DAPHNE:
It's okay, Shaggy...

03:00.765 --> 03:03.392
...Aunt Olivia will fix you something
in her apartment.

03:03.559 --> 03:05.227
If we ever get there, Daphne.

03:05.394 --> 03:07.146
We still can't get a cab.

03:07.355 --> 03:08.397
I'll get it.

03:08.606 --> 03:11.233
-You, Scoob, get a cab?
-Uh-huh.

03:14.820 --> 03:16.697
[WHISTLES]

03:18.074 --> 03:19.742
Yow!

03:21.535 --> 03:23.829
Watch out, Scooby,
you could get hurt.

03:24.038 --> 03:25.748
| am. | am.

03:25.956 --> 03:27.208
[CLATTERING]

03:27.375 --> 03:29.085
SHAGGY:
Like, what's going on in there?

03:29.251 --> 03:30.586
VELMA:
"Bixby Jewellers."

03:30.795 --> 03:32.588
The windows are all fogged up.

03:35.299 --> 03:36.342
[GROWLING]

03:36.509 --> 03:37.968
[SCREAMS]

03:38.135 --> 03:39.970
-What is it, Shaggy?
-Did you see something?

03:40.137 --> 03:42.973
Worse, something saw me.

03:43.140 --> 03:45.059
VELMA:
Something in the jewelry store?

03:45.267 --> 03:46.560
Let me have a look.

03:46.727 --> 03:49.980
It's horrible, Fred.
All that hair, all those teeth.

03:51.649 --> 03:53.818
FRED:
Well, there's nothing there now.

03:54.026 --> 03:56.487
But it looks like
something tore the place up.

03:58.989 --> 04:00.032
Yah!

04:00.199 --> 04:03.035
[SNARLING]

04:03.202 --> 04:04.245
[GASPS]

04:04.412 --> 04:06.664
[SNARLING]

04:08.999 --> 04:10.501
Hmm.

04:11.961 --> 04:13.921
Oh, no!

04:15.381 --> 04:16.464
SHAGGY:
Scooby.

04:16.632 --> 04:21.512
-Scooby-Doo, where are you?
-Oh!

04:23.889 --> 04:27.393
-Shaggy?
SHAGGY: Scooby.

04:29.311 --> 04:30.479
Down there.

04:30.646 --> 04:32.857
| saw this thing. It's a cat.

04:33.023 --> 04:34.567
It was awful.

04:34.733 --> 04:36.735
It was-- It was big like that.

04:36.902 --> 04:38.404
And he:

04:38.571 --> 04:39.989
A cat creature?

04:40.156 --> 04:42.825
-You saw it too?
-Oh, yeah, | did.

04:43.033 --> 04:45.119
[SIREN WAILING]

04:45.661 --> 04:47.580
The burglar alarm
rings in my apartment.

04:47.746 --> 04:50.416
That's when | called you.
I'd like you to check it out.

04:52.668 --> 04:55.588
VELMA: Mr. Bixby?
He must own the jewelry store.

04:55.796 --> 04:59.425
My entire collection of jewels,
completely wiped out.

04:59.633 --> 05:02.052
| don't care
about the rest of the jewels...

05:02.219 --> 05:04.180
...only the Richmond ruby.

05:04.346 --> 05:06.724
A cat creature, and a jewel theft.

05:06.891 --> 05:09.143
It looks like we've got a mystery
on our hands.

05:09.310 --> 05:11.937
Well,
| wash my hands of this whole thing.

05:12.438 --> 05:14.857
-Me too.
-Some cat-like creature...

05:15.024 --> 05:16.942
...must have tunneled into the store...

05:17.151 --> 05:20.613
...robbed the place,
then gone back out the same way.

05:20.779 --> 05:22.114
Where Scooby saw him.

05:22.740 --> 05:25.034
Let's check it out right now.

05:25.201 --> 05:27.495
That storm is moving pretty fast,
Velma.

05:27.661 --> 05:31.957
Like, right, let's get to Daphne's aunt's
place and check this out tomorrow.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.418
Hey.
Hey, what's this on your collar, Scoob?

05:34.627 --> 05:36.921
DAPHNE:
It looks like an emerald.

05:37.129 --> 05:40.007
Like, | told you never to accept gifts
from strangers.

05:40.216 --> 05:41.675
Especially cat creatures...

05:41.884 --> 05:44.178
...which is about as strange
as you can get.

05:50.351 --> 05:53.604
DRIVER:
Here it is, kids, York Towers.

05:53.812 --> 05:57.107
Strange things happen there.

05:57.274 --> 06:01.028
Some people go in
and never come out.

06:01.195 --> 06:02.363
[CHUCKLES]

06:02.530 --> 06:05.199
These New York cab drivers
really have a sense of humor.

06:05.407 --> 06:06.867
| wasn't joking.

06:07.076 --> 06:08.369
[LAUGHS]

06:08.536 --> 06:09.745
[CRYING]

06:09.912 --> 06:11.121
| was afraid of that.

06:11.330 --> 06:13.958
DAPHNE: Come on, Shaggy,
we'll get soaked out here.

06:14.124 --> 06:16.544
It's better than getting spooked
in there.

06:16.710 --> 06:19.922
Where do you think you're going?

06:20.089 --> 06:23.133
If I have a choice,
Palm Springs would be nice.

06:23.342 --> 06:26.554
My aunt lives here. Olivia Dervy.

06:26.762 --> 06:29.014
She expects you?

06:29.181 --> 06:31.141
DAPHNE:
Yes, can we go in now?

06:34.228 --> 06:37.231
Our valet will be along with our bags.

06:41.235 --> 06:43.195
Thank you.

06:44.280 --> 06:46.907
Oh, boy, an old cage elevator.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.076
They haven't built these in years.

06:49.285 --> 06:52.288
SHAGGY: Punch the top floor for us,
will you, Scoob?

06:56.792 --> 06:58.877
[GROWLING]

07:04.717 --> 07:06.093
DAPHNE:
She's got to be home.

07:06.302 --> 07:08.762
| wrote her we'd be arriving tonight.

07:09.179 --> 07:11.265
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

07:16.979 --> 07:19.023
What--? Where--?

07:19.189 --> 07:20.232
I'm coming.

07:20.399 --> 07:22.693
I'm coming.

07:25.988 --> 07:27.031
Who is it?

07:27.197 --> 07:29.366
It's me, Aunt Olivia, Daphne.

07:29.533 --> 07:30.909
And my friends.

07:31.076 --> 07:33.162
OLIVIA:
Daphne.

07:34.580 --> 07:37.374
Inside. Quickly.

07:40.336 --> 07:42.463
Strange things are happening, Daphne.

07:42.630 --> 07:44.298
You shouldn't have come.

07:44.506 --> 07:45.549
[BOTH GASP]

07:45.716 --> 07:47.676
Uh-- Strange happenings?

07:47.843 --> 07:49.970
Yeah, strange?

07:50.179 --> 07:51.764
OLIVIA:
You'll never believe me.

07:51.930 --> 07:53.182
I'll have to show you.

07:53.349 --> 07:55.142
Wait here.

07:59.021 --> 08:02.024
This jewelry wasn't here earlier.

08:02.232 --> 08:04.234
This place gives me the creeps.

08:04.401 --> 08:06.362
It's just old, Shaggy.

08:06.570 --> 08:08.822
Yeah, well, so was Count Dracula.

08:08.989 --> 08:10.699
OLIVIA:
I'd better start at the beginning.

08:10.908 --> 08:15.954
Two weeks ago,
a strange package was delivered.

08:16.413 --> 08:18.082
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

08:19.833 --> 08:22.544
Yes? What's this?

08:24.546 --> 08:30.469
| took the package inside, unwrapped it,
and found a strange medallion.

08:30.678 --> 08:32.221
It looked valuable...

08:32.388 --> 08:35.057
...and | assumed
someone had made a mistake.

08:35.265 --> 08:38.352
Thinking someone would claim it
| kept it.

08:38.519 --> 08:42.231
And, that night,
had an incredible nightmare.

08:43.273 --> 08:47.069
| dreamed | turned info...

08:47.236 --> 08:48.862
[SNARLING]

08:49.029 --> 08:51.865
...a cat creature.

08:53.951 --> 08:58.497
In this form,
I would go out and commit robberies.

08:58.664 --> 09:01.667
I couldn't help myself.

09:03.460 --> 09:06.922
And look what | found
in my room tonight.

09:07.131 --> 09:08.966
Look at this emerald earring.

09:09.133 --> 09:10.926
Just like the one Scooby found.

09:11.135 --> 09:13.470
Oh, my gosh. She is the cat creature.

09:13.637 --> 09:15.055
Let me out of here.

09:15.222 --> 09:17.099
Me too.

09:17.307 --> 09:20.060
DAPHNE: Scooby, Shaggy,
Aunt Olivia needs help.

09:20.269 --> 09:24.148
Yeah?
Well, we'll send the National Guard.

09:24.314 --> 09:25.733
[BOTH SCREAM]

09:26.525 --> 09:27.985
It's all right, children.

09:28.152 --> 09:31.071
This is my doctor, Dr. Bell.

09:31.989 --> 09:35.242
He's been treating
my nervous condition.

09:35.909 --> 09:39.413
Like, I'd be nervous too
if | was turning into a cat creature.

09:39.621 --> 09:41.290
Hey, what's this?

09:41.457 --> 09:45.753
Why, that's the wrapping paper
the cat medallion came in.

09:45.961 --> 09:47.504
FRED:
And it's got a return address.

09:47.713 --> 09:49.673
Miss Dervy,
we'll see if we can help you.

09:49.840 --> 09:52.009
That clue should give us a good start.

09:52.217 --> 09:54.970
VELMA:
Nice to have met you, Dr. Bell.

09:55.137 --> 09:57.556
Yes.

10:01.977 --> 10:05.230
Shaggy, the girls and |
will check out the return address.

10:05.397 --> 10:08.275
You and Scoob see what you can find
at the jewelry store.

10:08.484 --> 10:12.404
Like, there's no way I'm going back
to that jewelry store tonight, Fred.

10:12.571 --> 10:14.656
Then you
and Scooby check out the address...

10:14.823 --> 10:16.241
...and we'll go to the store.

10:16.408 --> 10:18.285
That's better.

10:19.453 --> 10:22.289
Boy, Scoob,
we sure put one over on them.

10:22.456 --> 10:23.540
Yeah.

10:23.707 --> 10:24.917
[BOTH LAUGH]

10:25.125 --> 10:27.586
This address
is only two blocks from the apartment.

10:27.753 --> 10:29.588
We'll be back in no time.

10:31.006 --> 10:35.636
Hey, here it is now,
"3056 East Westmore."

10:35.803 --> 10:37.262
And it's a--

10:37.971 --> 10:39.014
A cemetery.

10:39.181 --> 10:40.933
A cemetery?

10:41.517 --> 10:43.852
Oh, no.

10:47.356 --> 10:51.401
This prescription should help,
Miss Dervy.

10:51.568 --> 10:55.864
Thank you.
Thank you very much, Dr. Bell.

11:06.375 --> 11:08.460
[SNARLING]

11:18.470 --> 11:20.556
[THUNDER CRASHING]

11:22.224 --> 11:25.102
BIXBY: | don't really care
about getting all the jewels back...

11:25.310 --> 11:29.064
...just the most valuable piece,
the Richmond ruby.

11:29.231 --> 11:30.941
DAPHNE: Oh, how pretty.
FRED: Wow.

11:31.608 --> 11:33.277
We'd like to help you, Mr. Bixby.

11:33.485 --> 11:35.571
You mind if we check the store
for clues?

11:35.737 --> 11:37.030
Help yourselves.

11:37.197 --> 11:39.366
Don't bother locking up
when you leave.

11:39.533 --> 11:41.285
There's nothing left anyway.

11:41.493 --> 11:44.663
| didn't see anything like this
in Aunt Olivia's jewelry.

11:44.830 --> 11:46.748
Me neither. That's strange.

11:46.915 --> 11:48.292
VELMA:
So is this, Fred.

11:48.959 --> 11:52.796
I'll bet this is how the cat creature got in
and out.

11:52.963 --> 11:54.006
Good work, Velma.

11:54.172 --> 11:56.300
Let's check it out.

11:56.758 --> 11:59.011
Well, | guess we gotta check it out.

11:59.177 --> 12:00.220
You first, Scooby.

12:00.387 --> 12:01.430
Uh-uh.

12:01.597 --> 12:04.266
-You first.
-It's an old custom, Scoob.

12:04.433 --> 12:07.311
Dogs before chickens.

12:07.519 --> 12:09.605
[CLUCKING]

12:11.023 --> 12:14.067
Now, what would your father say
if he saw you like that?

12:17.613 --> 12:19.615
[CROWING]

12:21.700 --> 12:23.160
It's the cat creature.

12:23.327 --> 12:24.620
Run.

12:24.828 --> 12:25.996
[LAUGHS]

12:26.163 --> 12:29.166
It was only the gate. Oh!

12:29.333 --> 12:30.709
[CRASHING]

12:31.293 --> 12:33.879
Is anybody home?

12:34.046 --> 12:35.172
[LAUGHS]

12:35.339 --> 12:36.590
Isn't that funny, Scoob?

12:36.757 --> 12:39.092
-Who'd be home in a cemetery?
-Yeah.

12:39.301 --> 12:41.428
[LAUGHS]

12:43.347 --> 12:45.557
| don't get it.

12:47.059 --> 12:49.144
[SNARLING]

12:51.146 --> 12:55.233
The return address says 13-B.

12:56.193 --> 12:58.654
-Look.
-"Thirteen-B."

12:58.820 --> 13:01.365
| guess it's just ahead.

13:02.240 --> 13:03.825
Yow! It's the cat creature.

13:03.992 --> 13:06.328
[SCREAMS]

13:06.495 --> 13:08.580
Wait, Scoob. It's just a statue.

13:09.331 --> 13:11.959
It's only a marble statue.

13:12.125 --> 13:16.213
Oh, boy, this is one return address
| never wanna return to again.

13:16.380 --> 13:17.422
Let's get out of here.

13:20.926 --> 13:22.928
Wait, it's a statue.

13:25.681 --> 13:27.099
[GIGGLING]

13:27.265 --> 13:29.476
[SNARLING]

13:31.353 --> 13:35.774
Oh, Scooby, that's no statue,
that's the cat creature.

13:36.441 --> 13:38.068
[SNARLS]

13:38.235 --> 13:39.444
Run.

13:42.948 --> 13:45.033
[SNARLING]

13:45.701 --> 13:48.662
Reverse your engines, Scoob.

13:51.415 --> 13:55.752
Whoa! Let me off this merry-go-round.

14:03.010 --> 14:05.095
[CRASHING]

14:05.303 --> 14:07.389
[SNARLING]

14:11.727 --> 14:14.021
How far does this tunnel go?

14:14.187 --> 14:17.065
It seems like miles.

14:18.025 --> 14:20.110
[MEOWING]

14:22.529 --> 14:23.613
What was that?

14:23.780 --> 14:25.949
It sounded like a cat. Look.

14:26.158 --> 14:28.243
[MEOWING]

14:30.370 --> 14:32.372
DAPHNE:
It's the cat creature.

14:32.539 --> 14:33.582
[PURRING]

14:33.749 --> 14:35.542
[ALL SIGH]

14:35.709 --> 14:38.754
It's only an alley cat.

14:38.920 --> 14:41.673
If he got in,
there must be a way out up ahead.

14:41.882 --> 14:44.551
So let's find it.

14:47.763 --> 14:50.432
SHAGGY: See if you can find
the light switch, Scooby.

14:50.599 --> 14:52.684
-How's that?
-Like, close enough.

14:53.935 --> 14:55.854
-Yikes!
-Relax, Scoob.

14:56.021 --> 14:58.023
Relax, it's just another statue.

15:02.152 --> 15:03.695
The place is crawling with them.

15:04.196 --> 15:08.450
And listen to this,
"The cat creature who shall rise again.â€

15:10.202 --> 15:15.123
Don't look now, Scoob,
but | think he's rising now.

15:16.458 --> 15:18.210
[SCREAMING]

15:18.960 --> 15:20.879
SHAGGY:
Go away, whatever you are.

15:21.088 --> 15:22.839
Oh, my goodness, | can't look.

15:23.006 --> 15:24.216
Me neither.

15:31.348 --> 15:33.225
So this is where the tunnel leads.

15:33.391 --> 15:35.060
SHAGGY: Velma.
-Huh?

15:36.269 --> 15:39.231
Shaggy, Scooby.
What are you doing here?

15:39.397 --> 15:42.567
Resting, but not in peace.

15:43.068 --> 15:45.153
[GROWLING]

15:51.201 --> 15:53.286
[SNARLING]

15:54.538 --> 15:56.456
You mean, there's no way out?

15:56.623 --> 16:00.585
Like, there never was a big market
for tomb exits, Daphne.

16:00.752 --> 16:02.212
[LAUGHS]

16:02.379 --> 16:05.090
[CREATURE SNARLING]

16:08.385 --> 16:11.138
DAPHNE:
It's the cat creature.

16:15.308 --> 16:17.185
Run.

16:18.145 --> 16:21.106
[CREATURE SNARLING]

16:21.273 --> 16:22.315
It's got me.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.776
Scooby.

16:25.569 --> 16:27.654
Scooby-Doo.

16:27.821 --> 16:29.114
FRED:
This way, guys.

16:29.322 --> 16:31.533
We found the door.

16:31.700 --> 16:34.077
Like, let's use it.

16:36.204 --> 16:37.789
[SNARLING]

16:43.295 --> 16:45.088
SHAGGY:
Red-hot. Red-hots.

16:45.255 --> 16:49.259
Get your red-hot hot dogs right here.

16:50.844 --> 16:52.053
[GROWLS]

16:52.262 --> 16:54.181
Take my word, you'll love it, sir.

16:54.347 --> 16:55.390
A little ketchup.

16:55.557 --> 16:57.058
Ketchup.

16:57.225 --> 16:58.268
Mustard.

16:58.435 --> 16:59.811
Mustard.

17:00.020 --> 17:01.730
And some relish.

17:01.938 --> 17:03.982
Relish.

17:04.148 --> 17:05.233
There you go, sir.

17:05.442 --> 17:07.569
Bite right in.

17:08.862 --> 17:10.946
[SCREAMING]

17:12.699 --> 17:14.701
Stop in again any time, sir.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.536
Let's go, Scoob.

17:16.703 --> 17:19.873
Scooby-Doo.

17:23.210 --> 17:27.297
| think your Aunt Olivia
definitely has a problem, Daphne.

17:27.464 --> 17:29.591
VELMA:
Hey, where's Haskell, the door man?

17:29.758 --> 17:31.092
DAPHNE:
Probably on a break.

17:37.098 --> 17:39.851
Thank you for coming so quickly,
Dr. Bell.

17:40.018 --> 17:41.603
Yes, thank you.

17:41.811 --> 17:44.773
I-- I just don't know
what's happening to me.

17:44.981 --> 17:47.108
This prescription should help.

17:47.317 --> 17:51.446
I'll check back in the morning
and see how you are doing, Miss Dervy.

17:52.489 --> 17:54.783
Aunt Olivia, what's that in your hand?

17:54.991 --> 17:58.161
It-- It looks like a piece of cloth.

17:58.328 --> 18:00.247
This was ripped
from Shaggy's shirt by--

18:00.413 --> 18:01.873
The cat creature.

18:02.040 --> 18:04.000
Then it's true.

18:04.167 --> 18:06.461
| am the cat creature.

18:06.670 --> 18:08.296
Not necessarily, Miss Dervy.

18:08.463 --> 18:12.425
And I've got a plan to find out for sure
what's happening.

18:13.301 --> 18:14.344
Why us?

18:14.511 --> 18:15.887
Yeah, why us?

18:16.054 --> 18:18.974
Don't worry,
we'll be right outside the door.

18:19.140 --> 18:21.977
Besides, what better protection
against a cat creature...

18:22.143 --> 18:24.521
...than a guard dog?

18:25.689 --> 18:30.193
Yeah, but this guard dog
is a scaredy-cat.

18:30.360 --> 18:31.486
[THUNDER CRASHING]

18:31.653 --> 18:34.823
SHAGGY: Yikes! Scoob,
did you close the window?

18:34.990 --> 18:36.783
SCOOBY: No.
-1 think you better.

18:36.950 --> 18:38.743
Oh, why should I close...?

18:38.910 --> 18:40.996
[GRUMBLING]

18:44.541 --> 18:46.626
[WHIMPERING]

18:48.962 --> 18:50.964
[SNARLING]

18:51.506 --> 18:53.049
SCOOBY:
Shaggy?

18:53.216 --> 18:55.302
[SNARLING]

18:56.553 --> 18:58.805
Shaggy?

19:00.223 --> 19:01.641
Aah!

19:06.521 --> 19:09.190
Scooby-Doo.

19:13.695 --> 19:15.155
What's going on, Shaggy?

19:15.322 --> 19:17.240
Shaggy?

19:17.824 --> 19:18.908
DAPHNE:
Oh, no.

19:19.075 --> 19:22.037
Now, the cat creature's got Shaggy
and Scooby.

19:22.245 --> 19:24.331
[SNARLING]

19:29.419 --> 19:32.130
FRED:
Head for the stairs.

19:33.506 --> 19:34.632
Going down.

19:34.966 --> 19:37.052
[MAKING TAUNTING NOISES]

19:40.472 --> 19:42.557
[SNARLING]

19:43.183 --> 19:44.642
Faster. Faster.

19:48.271 --> 19:50.774
Help. Help.

19:50.982 --> 19:54.611
Oh, no, the creature's in the elevator
with Scooby.

19:54.819 --> 19:57.322
SCOOBY:
Help. Get me out of here.

19:57.489 --> 20:00.700
Help, help. Open the door. Let me out!

20:00.867 --> 20:02.911
VELMA:
We've got to get to the control box.

20:03.119 --> 20:06.081
Good idea, Velma.
We'll just boost the elevator's power...

20:07.457 --> 20:09.125
...and have Scooby down in no time.

20:10.752 --> 20:12.087
Going up.

20:12.295 --> 20:14.381
[SNARLING]

20:17.092 --> 20:18.426
Going down.

20:22.639 --> 20:24.724
[SNARLING]

20:31.314 --> 20:33.733
FRED: Good work, Scooby.
DAPHNE: You did it.

20:33.900 --> 20:36.694
ALL:
Dr. Bell?

20:38.488 --> 20:40.448
| don't understand.

20:40.657 --> 20:41.950
It's simple, Aunt Olivia.

20:42.158 --> 20:45.453
Dr. Bell was using you as a front
to commit his robberies.

20:45.662 --> 20:49.958
He hypnotized you with this medallion
into thinking you were the cat creature.

20:50.166 --> 20:52.794
And he sent that phony cat medallion.

20:52.961 --> 20:55.964
We know that because the handwriting
matches the handwriting...

20:56.131 --> 20:57.799
...on the prescription he gave us.

20:58.007 --> 21:00.510
But-- But why me?

21:00.677 --> 21:05.181
Because you responded to hypnosis
better than any other patient | ever had.

21:05.348 --> 21:06.391
It was a snap.

21:06.599 --> 21:10.895
He would leave enough jewels with you
to convince you that you were guilty...

21:11.104 --> 21:13.189
...but kept the valuable pieces
for himself.

21:13.356 --> 21:14.732
DAPHNE:
Like the Richmond ruby.

21:14.941 --> 21:17.777
But--
But where's your friend, Shaggy?

21:17.986 --> 21:20.822
This old place is full of secret rooms
and panels.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.740
Watch.

21:28.329 --> 21:30.415
[SNORING]

21:30.999 --> 21:32.250
[YAWNS]

21:32.417 --> 21:33.543
Hey, everybody.

21:33.710 --> 21:35.044
Like, what's going on?

21:35.253 --> 21:36.379
Shaggy.

21:37.297 --> 21:40.800
Oh! Shaggy, Shaggy. Oh!

21:40.967 --> 21:42.969
Oh, Shaggy.

21:43.136 --> 21:47.474
SHAGGY: Wait.
Hey, how do you stop this thing?

21:48.391 --> 21:50.768
Help.

21:50.935 --> 21:52.562
Shaggy. Scooby.

21:52.729 --> 21:54.439
SHAGGY:
We're okay, Fred.

21:54.606 --> 21:56.483
What are you doing out there?

21:56.691 --> 22:01.029
Oh, just hanging around, eh, Scoob?
Ha-ha-ha.

22:01.362 --> 22:02.405
Yeah.

22:02.572 --> 22:04.824
[LAUGHS]
